    <sTitle>Heat capacity, enthalpy and entropy of Li2CO3 at 303.15 to 563.15 K</sTitle>
    <sAbstract>Measurements of the heat capacity of lithium carbonate were carried out with a heat conduction calorimeter in the temperature range of 303.15 to 563.15 K at atmospheric pressure. The temperature dependence of the heat capacity is  Cp [J/ (mol K)] = 92.80 + 0.09T - 1.91xE6 T-2.  The thermodynamic functions with reference temperature 298.15 K, calculated in the same temperature range are  H(T) - H(298) [kJ/mol] = -48.92 + 0.14T + 6.68xE5 T-2 S(T) - S(298) [J/(mol K)] = -53.73 + 0.24T - 1.55xE6 T-2.</sAbstract>
